                <h3>Click selfies at Millennium Park</h3>

                <p class="text-justify">Take dozens of selfies at Millennium Park when you visit Chicago. Grant Park, which encompasses Millennium Park, is larger in the heart of Chicago. Randolph Street to the north, Michigan Avenue to the west, Columbus Drive to the east, and Monroe Street to the south define its perimeter. The sculpture Cloud Gate, weighing 110 tons, is the focal point of the installation. Its glossy stainless steel surface resembles liquid mercury. The park mirrors the environment, including the sky, the neighboring buildings, and the tourists who pass through its main arch. </p>


                <h3>At Buckingham Fountain, observe the water show</h3>

                <p class="text-justify">One of the largest fountains in the world is the Clarence Buckingham Memorial Fountain. The central fountain is encircled by four seahorses that stand in for the four states that border Lake Michigan. It is constructed in the renowned Art Deco style of the era. Every hour, from 8 am to 11 night, the fountain erupts into life. It pours 15,000 gallons of water through almost 200 nozzles per minute to provide a stunning display. If you're in this area in the evening, you must witness the water display with lights after sunset. </p>

